From: nvidia-driver-injector <noreply@example.invalid>
Date: 2026-05-12
Subject: [PATCH 0004/0007] tb-egpu: Q-watchdog Mode B detector (cluster P3)

Consolidates legacy patches 0014 (kthread), 0015 (basic sysfs counters),
and the S3 portion of 0023 (persistent detection state + sysfs) into a
single coherent Q-watchdog cluster.

Per-device kthread that periodically reads NV_PMC_BOOT_0 via direct
volatile MMIO. On 0xFFFFFFFF (dead-bus signature), declares the GPU
disconnected via os_pci_set_disconnected — same kernel propagation as
Q-active uses from the ioctl path, but driven by an active heartbeat
that fires regardless of which subsystem stalled. Closes the DMA-path
Mode B detection gap that Q-active alone misses; see docs/lever-catalog.md
(Lever Q) for the full taxonomy.

Inventory items applied:

- struct/function/sysfs/kthread/module-param renames per inventory
  Section P3:
    tb_egpu_qwatchdog_*           -> tb_egpu_qwd_*
    struct tb_egpu_qwatchdog      -> struct tb_egpu_qwd
    struct tb_egpu_qwatchdog_aer_snapshot
                                  -> struct tb_egpu_qwd_aer_snapshot
    kthread "aorus-qwd-<bdf>"     -> "tb-egpu-qwd-<bdf>"
    NVreg_TbEgpuWatchdog{Enable,IntervalMs}
                                  -> NVreg_TbEgpuQwd{Enable,IntervalMs}
    log prefix "AORUS Lever Q-watchdog: ..."
                                  -> "tb_egpu: qwd ..."

- File moves:
    kernel-open/nvidia/nv-qwatchdog.{c,h}
        -> kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-qwd.{c,h}

- Sysfs registration: 5 separate device_create_file / device_remove_file
  pairs collapsed to a single static const struct attribute_group plus
  sysfs_create_group / sysfs_remove_group calls.

- Volatile MMIO read uses READ_ONCE on the volatile pointer rather than
  a raw deref; the intentional bypass of osDevReadReg032 (the Q-active
  wrapper) is documented inline ("Q-watchdog firings are cleanly
  attributable in dmesg vs Q-active firings").

- TB_EGPU_QWD_DEAD_BUS_VALUE is documented as a kernel-open mirror of
  the RM-side TB_EGPU_DEAD_BUS_U32 introduced by cluster P1. kernel-open
  does not share the RM header search path; the one-line duplication is
  accepted (the value is a hardware PCIe signature, not a tunable).

Cross-cluster split (S3 telemetry):

- The Q-watchdog cluster (this patch, P3) owns the persistent detection
  state struct (last_detection_jiffies, last_pmc_boot_0, last_aer),
  the three S3 sysfs files, and populates the first two fields at
  detect time.

- The AER-capture helper (tb_egpu_dump_aer_trigger_event) and its
  invocation from the Q-watchdog detect path live in cluster P2
  (nv-lever-m-recover.{c,h}). P2 will patch the detect-path inside
  tb_egpu_qwd_thread to add the one-line call:

      tb_egpu_dump_aer_trigger_event(nvl->pci_dev,
                                     "qwd-detect",
                                     &qwd->last_aer);

  Until P2 lands, last_aer.valid stays 0 and the
  tb_egpu_qwd_last_aer_summary sysfs reader politely reports
  "(no detection event yet)". The rest of Q-watchdog functions
  standalone on top of P1 + P5.

Dependencies:
- P1 (cluster 0001) — naming convention + crash-safety header
- P5 (cluster 0002) — applies cleanly before this patch, but no symbol
  dependency

Files touched:
  kernel-open/common/inc/nv-linux.h        +7  (qwd member)
  kernel-open/nvidia/nv-pci.c              +22 (init/stop call sites)
  kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-qwd.h       new (struct + decls)
  kernel-open/nvidia/nv-tb-egpu-qwd.c       new (kthread + sysfs)
  kernel-open/nvidia/nvidia-sources.Kbuild  +1  (source entry)

Note: README.md line 236 still references the old sysfs prefix
